Dear Sir or Madam,
I would like to ask you if you would consider giving me financial support to enable me to take up my place at the Royal Academy of Music in September 2011.
According to the enclosed letter of 2 February 2011 from the Royal Academy Music, the whole cost of study for the Academic Year 2011 - 2012 is 28,750GBP. My tuition fees are 18,750GBP, and my living expenses are 10,000GBP. I have been able to raise 11,000GBP. However, I still need to raise another 17,750GBP to cover the whole cost.
Given the opportunity to further my studies at the Royal Academy of Music, I feel sure I can go on to enjoy an international career at the highest level, with due credit to my supporters.
I will be grateful for any help you can give me at this important stage of my career.
lender.occupational_info:
I studied at the Kharkiv National Kotlyarevsky University of Arts with Professor Volodymyr Dotsenko and completed my Bachelor's Degree with Distinction in 2010. I have won several national and international prizes and given many recitals in many countries, including Ukraine, Poland, United Kingdom and Russia. I have also been a solo performer with various symphony orchestras and ensembles, such as the Kharkiv Philharmonic Academic Symphony Orchestra, Kharkiv National Kotlyarevsky University of Arts Symphony Orchestra and Kharkiv Guitar Quartet.
I have a close working relationship with a new generation of guitar composers, such as Vitaliy Kharisov and Konstantin Bliokh, giving first performances of new works and encouraging the development of the instrument's repertoire.
Given the opportunity to further my studies at the Royal Academy of Music, I feel sure I can go on to enjoy an international career at the highest level, with due credit to my supporters.
